Here, we look for the wonderful, amazingly-small vineyards of the noblest soil of the Cote d’Or, which produce only enough cases each year to whet the world’s appetite rather than satisfy it. These are the most difficult wines of all to obtain, because the grower rations his production among old friends and persuasion rather than money determines who will be the lucky ones.

Here are the treasures of Burgundy; masterpieces in any library of wines; with great potential to mature gracefully within your home — wines that can bring you joy for the next
